<div class="col-xs-12">
<h5 style="color:white;">
    Build Gridcoin Daemon<a name="build_gridcoin"></a>
</h5>
<ul style="list-style-type: none;">
<li>
Clone the latest Gridcoin-Research release using git:
</li>
<li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
cd ~ git clone <a class="external free" href="https://github.com/gridcoin/Gridcoin-Research" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/gridcoin/Gridcoin-Research</a>
</pre>
</li>
<li style="padding-bottom:15px; padding-left:15px;">
    <span class="label label-success" style="color:black;">Updating?</span> If you already have Gridcoin installed & you're updating, do this:
</li>
<li style="padding-left:15px;">
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
git pull
</li>
<li style="padding-bottom:5px; padding-left:15px; padding-bottom:15px;">
    <span class="label label-warning" style="color:black;">
        Having trouble updating source from git? Execute:
    </span>
</li>
<li style="padding-left:15px;">
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
git config --global
http.sslverify false
</pre>
</li>
<li>
Continue the setup process in the terminal:
</li>
<li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">mkdir ~/Gridcoin-Research/src/obj && cd ~/Gridcoin-Research/src && chmod 755 leveldb/build_detect_platform && make -f makefile.unix USE_UPNP=-</pre>
<li>
<li style="padding-bottom:10px;">
 If you encounter build errors relating to zerocoin dependencies, click <a href="">here</a>.
</li>
</ul>
</div>

<div class="col-xs-12">
<ul style="list-style-type: none; padding-left:15px;">
    <li>
        The gridcoind will be found in the /src directory
    </li>
    <li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">strip gridcoinresearchd
sudo install -m 755 gridcoinresearchd
/usr/bin/gridcoinresearchd
</pre>
    </li>
    <li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">mkdir ~/.GridcoinResearch
cd ~/
chmod 700 .GridcoinResearch
cd .GridcoinResearch
</pre>
    </li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="row" style="text-align:left;">

<div class="col-xs-12">
<h5 style="color:white;">
    Creating config file<a name="config"></a>
</h5>

<ul style="list-style-type: none; padding-left:15px;">
<li>
    Execute this command in the terminal:
</li>
<li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
nano ~/.GridcoinResearch/gridcoinresearch.conf
</pre>
</li>
<li>
    Copy and paste the following into the file:
</li>
<li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
email=&lt;your email, must match your BOINC projects&gt;
server=1
daemon=1
rpcallowip=127.0.0.1
rpcuser=&lt;username (anything you want, does not need to match BOINC)&gt;
rpcpassword=&lt;password (anything you want, does not need to match BOINC)&gt;
addnode=node.gridcoin.us
</pre>
</li>
<li>
    If you chose the "nano" command line editor, press CTRL+O to write the file
    information, and then CTRL+X to exit. For any other editor, just save the file
    and exit. To test type:
</li>
<li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
gridcoinresearchd
</pre>
</li>
<li>
Wait for the server to start and then type:
</li>
<li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
gridcoinresearchd getmininginfo
</pre>
</li>
<li>
    This should return the current difficulty and other network settings.
</li>
</ul>
</div>


</div>



<div class="row" style="text-align:left;">

<div class="col-xs-12">
<h5 style="color:white;">
    SSL (optional)<a name="SSL"></a>
</h5>

<ul style="list-style-type: none; padding-left:15px;">
    <li>
        You really only need SSL if you are controlling Gridcoin directly from another host. This does not apply to most people, even if you are using ssh from another computer. If you are not sure that you need this, then skip this section.
    </li>
    <li>
        First, add this line to gridcoinresearch.conf
    </li>
    <li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
rpcssl=1
</pre>
    </li>
    <li>
        Then, run these commands in your shell:
    </li>
    <li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
cd ~/.GridcoinResearch
openssl genrsa -out server.pem 2048
openssl req -new -x509 -nodes -sha1 -days 3650 -key server.pem &gt; server.cert
</pre>
    </li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="row" style="text-align:left;">

<div class="col-xs-12">
<h5 style="color:white;">
    Build Gridcoin-Qt<a name="QT"></a>
</h5>

<ul style="list-style-type: none; padding-left:15px;">
    <li>
        Navigate to the directory where gridcoinstake.pro is located:
    </li>
    <li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
cd ~/Gridcoin-Research
</pre>
    </li>
    <li>
        IMPORTANT: now edit gridcoinstake.pro and remove the entries "QT += qaxcontainer" and "CONFIG += qaxcontainer":
    </li>
    <li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
nano gridcoinstake.pro
</pre>
    </li>
    <li>
        if you have built Gridcoin-Qt previously, do:
    </li>
<li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
rm -f build/o.*
</pre>
</li>
    <li>
        If this is an initial installation of Gridcoin-Qt:
    </li>
<li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
qmake "USE_UPNP=-"
</pre>
</li>
<li>
    Look for gridcoinresearch, it should be in the current folder.
</li>
<li>
<pre style="max-width:750px;">
make
strip gridcoinresearch
sudo install -m 755 gridcoinresearch /usr/bin/gridcoinresearch
</pre>
</li>
<li>
    Verify wallet finds nodes and starts syncing
</li>
</ul>
